author: Associated Press
title: College football: Stanford, Cal climb in AP poll
text:
College football: Stanford, Cal climb in AP poll Associated Press Posted: 10/04/2015 05:31:07 PM PDT Updated: 10/04/2015 05:31:09 PM PDT Stanford and Cal moved up in The Associated Press college football Top 25 on Sunday, a day after posting home victories. 
The Cardinal (4-1) jumped two spots to No. 16 after routing Arizona 55-17 for its fourth straight win. The Bears (5-0) moved up one position to No. 23 after beating Washington State 34-28. 
Ohio State remained No. 1 and tied a poll record, despite lagging support from the voters. The Buckeyes held off Indiana 34-27 and now have been top-ranked 101 times, matching Oklahoma for the most in the 79-year history of the media poll. 
After four top-10 teams lost Saturday, the rankings were rattled and five teams received first-place votes. The Buckeyes received 38 first-place votes, their fewest this season after beginning as the first unanimous preseason No. 1. No. 2 TCU got five first-place votes, No. 3 Baylor received 10, No. 5 Utah had seven, and No. 9 Texas A&M had one. 
The Utes (4-0), who jumped five spots after their bye week, will play host to Cal on Saturday night. 
Both Bay Area teams climbed two spots in the coaches poll, with Stanford landing at No. 18 and Cal at No. 22. Georgia: Coach Mark Richt says he's sticking with Greyson Lambert as the Bulldogs starting quarterback. Lambert completed just 10 of 24 passes for 86 yards in a 38-10 loss to Alabama. Brice Ramsey also got some playing time, but he completed only one pass and had two interceptions. Advertisement 
Texas: Cornerback Kris Boyd has apologized for being on Twitter during halftime of an embarrassing 50-7 loss to No. 3 TCU, when he passed along a suggestion that he transfer to Texas A&M. The freshman said in a statement issued by the university that "in no way did I intend to be disrespectful or disloyal" when he retweeted what amounted to an invitation to transfer from an apparent supporter of the Aggies, a rival the Longhorns don't play anymore.
